history.content:
I was wondering which course between 160 and 169 would provide a greater number of skills needed in order to pass resume screens for most internships/jobs. It seems that a lot of internships nowadays require a lot of frontend exposure, and I know very little about frontend. I'm not sure how in-depth 160 goes into the same and was wondering if taking 160 would help in that regard. I've heard 169, while demanding, also teaches what you can get from an internship, but if I don't have an internship yet, then I was wondering if I should take the course if it can provide me with projects/skills that can supplement my resume and help me get past the resume screening process?

I was also wondering which courses provide the most frontend exposure, if not 160. Or do we not have a CS elective that goes into frontend at Cal?
history.subject: 160 vs 169?
